1) tar : Create or extract archive files
    Options:
    * -c : Create a new archive
    * -x : Extract files from an archive
    * -f : Specify the archive file name
    * -v : verbose mode
    * -z : Compress the archive with gzip 
    * -j : Compress the archive with bzip2
    Example:  tar -czvf archive.tar.gz file/
              Creates a compressed tar archive named "archive.tar.gz" containing the files in the "files/" dir

2) gzip : Compress files
    Options:
      * -d : Decompress files
    Example: gzip file.txt => compresses the file "file.txt" and renames it as "file.txt.gz".

3) zip : create compressed zip archives
    Options:
      * -r : recursively include directories
    Example: zip archive.zip file1.txt file2.txt 
              creates a zip archive named "archive.zip" containing "file1.txt" and "file2.txt"
